## Obligations

1. The Counterparty shall perform the services described in the *Statement of Work* with reasonable skill and care.
2. The Company shall pay the agreed fees within thirty days of receipt of a valid invoice.
3. Both parties shall keep the other's confidential information confidential per the *Confidentiality* clause below.
4. Both parties shall comply with applicable law, including the *Data Protection* clause below.

## Confidentiality

Each party shall keep confidential the other's confidential information for the duration of this agreement and for **{{TODO_CONFIDENTIALITY_YEARS}}** years thereafter, except where disclosure is required by law or by a court of competent jurisdiction.

Confidential information does not include information that is in the public domain other than through the breach of this clause, or that the receiving party can show was in its possession before disclosure.

## Intellectual property

All intellectual property created by the Counterparty in the course of the services vests in the Company on creation. The Counterparty waives any moral rights in such intellectual property to the extent permitted by law and undertakes to execute any further documents the Company reasonably requests to perfect this assignment.

The Counterparty's pre-existing intellectual property remains the Counterparty's; the Counterparty grants the Company a perpetual, royalty-free licence to use such pre-existing intellectual property to the extent it is incorporated in the deliverables.

## Limitation of liability

Neither party excludes or limits liability for (a) death or personal injury caused by negligence, (b) fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation, or (c) any other liability that cannot lawfully be limited.

Subject to the above, each party's aggregate liability under this agreement in any twelve-month period is limited to the fees paid or payable under this agreement in that period.

## Termination

Either party may terminate this agreement for material unremedied breach, for insolvency of the other party, or on the notice period set out in the *Term* clause above.

On termination the Counterparty shall return or destroy the Company's confidential information and shall hand over any deliverables in progress. Clauses that by their nature are intended to survive termination — *Confidentiality*, *IP*, *Limitation of Liability* — do so.

## Governing law and jurisdiction

This agreement is governed by the laws of England and Wales. The parties submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales for any dispute arising out of or in connection with this agreement.

